426	20	Student	Female	I believe the goal was to study human perception towards someone based on their previous actions. Also the test studied how we guess a person's future behavior based on their previous course of actions. It further evaluated the time needed and rate of accuracy of cognitive functions of a person after they have studied both Bob's good and bad traits.	Even though it is a test of cognitive learning someone like me will not heavily rely on someone's past actions as I believe human beings are unpredictable and complex. So, the set of questions in the beginning all portraying negative aspects and the second set portraying all positive aspects is more like detecting a pattern rather than detecting any characteristics of Bob. 